.TH motd "" "" "System Administration"
.PC "File that holds message of the day"
\fB/etc/motd\fR
.PP
.II "message of the day"
The file
.B motd
holds the message of the day.
Its contents are displayed by the script
.BR /etc/profile ,
which is executed whenever you log in.
.PP
Only the superuser can alter the contents of this file.
.SH "See Also"
.Xr "Administering COHERENT," administe
.Xr "login" login
